1
00:00:07,666 --> 00:00:09,666
♪

2
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:20,666
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,416
♪

4
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,583
[SAIKI]
It's that time of the year

5
00:01:45,666 --> 00:01:47,750
when excitement runs through
every school.

6
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,041
That's because it's
time for

7
00:01:49,125 --> 00:01:50,791
one of high school's
biggest events,

8
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:52,208
The school trip.

9
00:01:52,291 --> 00:01:54,416
[GIRL] I've never been
to Okinawa before.

10
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,833
This year we're going on
a 3-day trip to Okinawa.

11
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:57,916
You think
it's hot there?

12
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,166
It's a southern
island!

13
00:01:59,250 --> 00:02:00,625
Seriously?
I don't get the appeal

14
00:02:00,708 --> 00:02:01,916
of these trips at all.

15
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,625
I can go to Okinawa
and come back

16
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:04,916
within three minutes.

17
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,500
Saiki, have you picked
your group

18
00:02:06,583 --> 00:02:08,041
for the trip?
It's gotta be a total

19
00:02:08,125 --> 00:02:09,416
of three boys
and three s.

20
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,666
Let everyone else
decide.

21
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:12,208
I'll just go
with whoever's left.

22
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:13,500
Looks like
the only ones

23
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:15,250
besides you
are Nendou and Kaidou.

24
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:16,958
Guess the best weren't
saved for last.

25
00:02:17,041 --> 00:02:18,291
That's three boys.
Perfect!

26
00:02:18,375 --> 00:02:19,666
I'll mark you down
as a group.

27
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:21,291
Let me know once
you find three s.

28
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:22,958
Now I'm even less
excited about going.

29
00:02:23,041 --> 00:02:24,791
Especially since--

30
00:02:24,875 --> 00:02:27,250
Saiki's gonna be with
those two guys after all.

31
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:28,708
Just as we suspected.

32
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:30,625
The only thing that
we have to figure out

33
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:32,541
is how we're going
to join up with them.

34
00:02:32,625 --> 00:02:34,791
I'd be way too embarrassed to
ask them directly.

35
00:02:34,875 --> 00:02:36,000
Oh, I know!

36
00:02:36,083 --> 00:02:37,250
Why don't we have
Mera do it!

37
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:38,500
Chisato's out today.

38
00:02:38,583 --> 00:02:39,958
[YUMEHARA]
I heard she's working

39
00:02:40,041 --> 00:02:41,125
to earn money for
the trip.

40
00:02:41,208 --> 00:02:42,750
[TERUHASHI] Ugh,
sounds rough.

41
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:44,958
[YUMEHARA] Got a postcard from
her yesterday. See?

42
00:02:45,041 --> 00:02:48,000
[TERUHASHI] Tuna? Whoa.
So what should we do?

43
00:02:48,083 --> 00:02:49,208
There's no other
option.

44
00:02:49,291 --> 00:02:50,791
I'll have
to ask Kaidou myself!

45
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:53,208
[TERUHASHI] Whoa, she's gonna
ask the guy she likes?

46
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:54,583
That's pretty
forward.

47
00:02:54,666 --> 00:02:56,583
[NARRATOR]
Teruhashi's under the impression

48
00:02:56,666 --> 00:02:57,875
that Yumehara likes Kaidou.

49
00:02:57,958 --> 00:02:59,291
She could not be more wrong.

50
00:02:59,375 --> 00:03:01,041
Oh, no, I don't see
Kaidou anywhere.

51
00:03:01,125 --> 00:03:02,416
That's okay,
I can ask Nendou.

52
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:03,750
He's right over
there.

53
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,375
Whoa, she's asking
the guy she likes?

54
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:06,791
[TERUHASHI] The 's got
guts!

55
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:08,500
[NARRATOR]
Yumehara thinks Teruhashi

56
00:03:08,583 --> 00:03:10,250
likes Nendou.
She is also very wrong.

57
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:11,583
[YUMEHARA] Hey, Nendou, wait!

58
00:03:11,666 --> 00:03:13,875
[excited chatter]

59
00:03:13,958 --> 00:03:15,750
[giggles]
I can't ask

60
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:17,916
to join Nendou's group
with all these guys around.

61
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,041
[SAIKI] Hm! If you did that,
Yumehara wouldn't be

62
00:03:20,125 --> 00:03:21,583
the only one
with the wrong idea.

63
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:23,125
Uh, what's goin' on?

64
00:03:23,208 --> 00:03:25,291
[SAIKI] Teruhashi's too popular
for her own good.

65
00:03:25,375 --> 00:03:27,458
I have relatives in Okinawa.
I can show you around!

66
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:29,583
I used to live in Okinawa
and they called me

67
00:03:29,666 --> 00:03:31,541
"Islanders' Treasure"
when I was little!

68
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:33,291
I'm friends with
Bi Kyo Ran's bassist!

69
00:03:33,375 --> 00:03:35,250
[BOY 1] Liar!
[BOY 2] They're from Shizuoka!

70
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:36,833
We have no choice.
We'll decide

71
00:03:36,916 --> 00:03:38,958
the boy/girl match-ups
via random draw.

72
00:03:39,041 --> 00:03:40,583
Teruhashi, you're up.

73
00:03:40,666 --> 00:03:42,000
[TERUHASHI] Aw, this stinks.

74
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:43,750
I have to depend
on blind luck.

75
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:45,750
Then again,
God does adore me.

76
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:47,583
A one-in-six chance
tipped in my favor

77
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:48,916
isn't too much to ask.

78
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,958
Just gotta use
those puppy-dog eyes.

79
00:03:51,041 --> 00:03:52,875
Please let me pick
Saiki!

80
00:03:52,958 --> 00:03:54,041
Okay!

81
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:55,500
I've got this in
the bag!

82
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:56,958
[SAIKI] It's truly frightening

83
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:58,666
how she always gets
what she wants.

84
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:01,333
Too bad for her, though.
Puppy-dog eyes don't work on me.

85
00:04:01,416 --> 00:04:03,791
[TERUHASHI] I pick this one!

86
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:05,416
So then,
Teruhashi's group

87
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,458
will be joining
Takahashi's group!

88
00:04:07,541 --> 00:04:08,875
[group giggling]

89
00:04:08,958 --> 00:04:10,958
[TAKAHASHI]
If you wanna talk to Teruhashi,

90
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:12,333
you'll have to go through me.

91
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:14,208
Guess we can play
board games or something

92
00:04:14,291 --> 00:04:15,500
when we're at
the hotel.

93
00:04:15,583 --> 00:04:16,875
Yeah, I'll bring
<i>Uno</i> with me.

94
00:04:16,958 --> 00:04:19,083
We know which guys
Teruhashi is going with,

95
00:04:19,166 --> 00:04:21,083
but what about the rest
of the s' groups?

96
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:22,375
Shall we keep drawing
names?

97
00:04:22,458 --> 00:04:24,458
[muttering]

98
00:04:24,541 --> 00:04:26,333
[HAIRO] Talk about a drop
in enthusiasm.

99
00:04:26,416 --> 00:04:27,583
[SAIKI]
The groups were set

100
00:04:27,666 --> 00:04:28,875
to be paired
by lottery, but--

101
00:04:28,958 --> 00:04:30,250
[GIRL 2] Nendou's group?
Ew.

102
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:32,250
Can we, like,
pick again or something?

103
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:35,083
This totes bums us out and ruins
the whole trip for us!

104
00:04:35,166 --> 00:04:36,208
That's kinda harsh.

105
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:37,625
That's
going far.

106
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:39,375
[SAIKI] I don't care
who we wind up with,

107
00:04:39,458 --> 00:04:41,166
as long as it's not
Teruhashi's group.

108
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:43,000
I want to switch!
Teruhashi!

109
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:44,250
[SAIKI] Damn it.

110
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:45,791
If Nendou and the others
don't mind.

111
00:04:45,875 --> 00:04:47,208
[TERUHASHI] This is perfect!

112
00:04:47,291 --> 00:04:49,000
Normally, wanting to join
Nendou's group

113
00:04:49,083 --> 00:04:50,208
would seem strange, but--

114
00:04:50,291 --> 00:04:51,666
Come on, stupid,
don't you get it?

115
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,208
[SAIKI] Yeah,
in this situation...

116
00:04:53,291 --> 00:04:54,708
She's sticking up
for Nendou!

117
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:55,916
So selfless!

118
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,375
That's Teruhashi
for you!

119
00:04:57,458 --> 00:04:58,875
[ALL]
That's our Teruhashi,

120
00:04:58,958 --> 00:05:00,125
you're a benevolent goddess!

121
00:05:00,208 --> 00:05:01,583
This doesn't just
make sense,

122
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:03,458
it actually makes me
more likable.

123
00:05:03,541 --> 00:05:05,125
We're gonna have fun
together!

124
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:06,625
[SAIKI] God loves her
way too much.

125
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:08,583
We just dodged
a major bullet, s!

126
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:10,875
We can dig holes in
the sand during our downtime.

127
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:12,083
All day long.

128
00:05:12,166 --> 00:05:14,000
Hairo, can we talk?
Ms. Shima?

129
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:15,416
[HAIRO]
Who's in Mera's group?

130
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,833
Oh, right here!
That'd be us!

131
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:19,000
Sorry, but she can't go
on the trip.

132
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,708
What?
They couldn't catch

133
00:05:20,791 --> 00:05:22,625
as many tuna
as they'd hoped.

134
00:05:22,708 --> 00:05:24,000
An unfortunate setback.

135
00:05:24,083 --> 00:05:25,458
[GIRL 3] Tuna?
[BOY 3] Seriously?

136
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:26,875
[GIRL 4] Too bad.
Oh, I see.

137
00:05:26,958 --> 00:05:28,208
That really is a shame.

138
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:29,500
That means
we'll be forming

139
00:05:29,583 --> 00:05:31,208
five groups
of seven instead, okay?

140
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:32,500
[both scream]

141
00:05:32,583 --> 00:05:34,125
[HAIRO]
Let's have each member

142
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:36,291
of Teruhashi's group
join another group.

143
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:38,000
[BOY 4]
Please pick us, Teruhashi!

144
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:39,625
[BOY 5]
Please, I need this!

145
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:41,875
[SAIKI] Looks like God's on my
side this time.

146
00:05:41,958 --> 00:05:44,875
♪

147
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:48,333
[KUNIHARU]
Your school trip's

148
00:05:48,416 --> 00:05:49,541
next week, huh?

149
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:50,916
I want you
to be careful, okay.

150
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,416
Nendou and Kaidou
will be with you,

151
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,875
so there's no
cause for concern.

152
00:05:53,958 --> 00:05:55,791
[SAIKI] They're the definition
of concern.

153
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,375
[KUNIHARU] Two nights?
Try not to use

154
00:05:57,458 --> 00:05:59,208
your powers in your sleep.
[SAIKI] I won't.

155
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:00,541
Remember
how you did that

156
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:01,791
up until
the fourth grade?

157
00:06:01,875 --> 00:06:03,000
We had to clean up

158
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,583
after your
nighttime accidents.

159
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:06,541
[SAIKI] Don't make it sound
like I wet the bed.

160
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:08,166
Anyway, I'm glad things
worked out

161
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,541
and my group got
split up,

162
00:06:09,625 --> 00:06:11,375
though I do feel
kind of bad for Mera.

163
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:12,625
[doorbell rings]

164
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:14,000
Wonder who that
could be.

165
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:15,166
I'll get it.

166
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:16,541
[SAIKI] Oh, come on.

167
00:06:16,625 --> 00:06:18,291
Are you going on vacation
with Kokomi?

168
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:20,541
[SAIKI] This is Makoto,
Teruhashi's older brother.

169
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:22,291
Hey, what are you
looking at?

170
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,500
[SAIKI] He may be a big star,
but he's also a big perv,

171
00:06:24,583 --> 00:06:25,708
so I don't wanna
talk to him.

172
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:27,208
Answer me! Is it true

173
00:06:27,291 --> 00:06:29,125
that you're taking
my sister on a three-day,

174
00:06:29,208 --> 00:06:30,833
two-night trip!
[SAIKI] A school trip.

175
00:06:30,916 --> 00:06:32,083
She's only
in the 11th grade!

176
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:33,458
[SAIKI] Hence the school trip.

177
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:35,125
[MAKOTO] There's gonna be
other guys?

178
00:06:35,208 --> 00:06:36,250
[SAIKI] School trip.

179
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:37,750
What will you do
to my Kokomi,

180
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,083
you pervy
four-eyed freak?

181
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,333
[SAIKI] You're the perv.

182
00:06:40,416 --> 00:06:42,250
Shut up! Stop trying
to mess with me!

183
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:44,000
[SAIKI] You're the one
messing with me.

184
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:45,541
Fine, if you guys
insist on going,

185
00:06:45,625 --> 00:06:47,083
then I'm going,
too.

186
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:49,750
Hah-hah-hah! It's too bad
for you, four-eyes!

187
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,666
Bet you were hoping
to spy on her bathing,

188
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,250
but now you won't get
the chance!

189
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:54,541
[SAIKI] I had no such plans.

190
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:56,333
Can't fool me!
I know you were planning

191
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,208
to sneak into the girls room,
and then,

192
00:06:58,291 --> 00:06:59,750
when a patrolling teacher
comes by,

193
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:01,458
try to hide,
only to find yourself

194
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:03,000
under the covers
with Kokomi!

195
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:05,000
My presence there means
you're out of luck!

196
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:06,708
[SAIKI] That was a little
too detailed.

197
00:07:06,791 --> 00:07:09,208
I'm going, even if it
means skipping <i>Oha-suta</i>

198
00:07:09,291 --> 00:07:11,291
and <i>World Business Satellite!</i>
 [laughs]

199
00:07:11,375 --> 00:07:13,125
[SAIKI] TV Tokyo won't be happy
about that.

200
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:14,250
Here I was relieved

201
00:07:14,333 --> 00:07:15,833
when the groups
were changed up,

202
00:07:15,916 --> 00:07:17,833
but if he tags along,
the trip'll be ruined.

203
00:07:17,916 --> 00:07:19,458
I'll just have
to let his manager know

204
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:21,291
about his plans
to miss out on work.

205
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:22,833
[LITTLE GIRL]
Cheer up, sis!

206
00:07:22,916 --> 00:07:24,500
But I really wanted
to go on that trip.

207
00:07:24,583 --> 00:07:25,875
You can
go next time!

208
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:28,166
[MERA] This trip's
once-in-a-lifetime.

209
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:29,791
Please don't be
so sad.

210
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:31,750
At least they let you
take this fish home!

211
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:34,000
I guess, but it's the ugliest
fish I've ever seen.

212
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:36,416
[MERA]
Wish I could go to Okinawa.

213
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,666
[SAIKI]
All right, Teruhashi. You win.

214
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:39,750
[MERA]
Huh? Saiki?

215
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:42,291
[SAIKI]
There's a saying:

216
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:43,791
"Trips and troubles
go together."

217
00:07:43,875 --> 00:07:45,083
What are we
gonna do, sir?

218
00:07:45,166 --> 00:07:46,375
This doesn't
look good.

219
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:48,625
[SAIKI]
We learned that the hard way.

220
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,041
[LADY]
<i>Due to a typhoon,</i>

221
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:51,500
<i>the 10 o'clock flight</i>
<i>to Okinawa</i>

222
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:52,833
<i>is temporarily</i>
<i>suspended.</i>

223
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:54,625
[SAIKI]
That's right. Our school trip

224
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,250
may be over
before it even begins.

225
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:57,916
Not 10 minutes ago,
these kids

226
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,416
were experiencing
pure joy--

227
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,083
[STUDENT] I can't wait
to get there!

228
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,333
[SAIKI] --then we heard about
the typhoon, and boom,

229
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,291
those same kids were
like this.

230
00:08:05,375 --> 00:08:06,958
I've never seen
extreme joy

231
00:08:07,041 --> 00:08:09,041
turn to extreme sorrow
so suddenly.

232
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:10,916
They're in the depths
of despair.

233
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,791
And just when
I was finally able to go.

234
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:15,375
[TERUHASHI] I was finally
able to be in Saiki's group.

235
00:08:15,458 --> 00:08:16,625
[SAIKI] And look at this guy.

236
00:08:16,708 --> 00:08:18,250
[scoffs]
School trips are so lame.

237
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:20,125
We should skip it.
Whaddaya say?

238
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,833
[SAIKI] That was him bluffing
earlier.

239
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:23,416
But really,
he's been dying to go.

240
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:26,125
You can clearly see
the circles under his eyes.

241
00:08:26,208 --> 00:08:28,458
I bet he was too excited
to sleep last night.

242
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:29,958
And take Yumehara.

243
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:31,541
I bought snacks
for the trip!

244
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:32,791
[GIRL 5] That's way too much!

245
00:08:32,875 --> 00:08:34,208
[SAIKI]
Before, she showed off

246
00:08:34,291 --> 00:08:36,208
all the food she brought
to eat on the plane.

247
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:39,083
Now she's eating everything
with a blank stare on her face.

248
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:40,875
Then there's Nendou.

249
00:08:40,958 --> 00:08:43,166
Blonde babes everywhere
and shooting guns!

250
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:45,125
[SAIKI] Putting aside
that he thinks Okinawa

251
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:47,041
is a foreign country,
he was pretty excited.

252
00:08:47,125 --> 00:08:48,208
But now look at him.

253
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:49,500
Temporarily suspended?

254
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:51,750
Tem-poo-rarily
rear-ended!

255
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,833
[SAIKI] He still can't face
reality.

256
00:08:53,916 --> 00:08:56,500
If the flight's canceled,
will the trip be postponed?

257
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:57,750
No! It'll be canceled.

258
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,500
You may not care,
but we've been

259
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,333
looking forward to this
forever and--

260
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:02,458
[ALL] Uno?

261
00:09:02,541 --> 00:09:03,875
I do want you kids to go,

262
00:09:03,958 --> 00:09:05,416
but it's out of my hands now.

263
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:06,958
[GIRL 6] Mister Matsuzaki,
no!

264
00:09:07,041 --> 00:09:08,625
[SAIKI] This is brutal.

265
00:09:08,708 --> 00:09:09,833
Don't give up hope, guys!

266
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,375
The flight's not canceled yet!

267
00:09:11,458 --> 00:09:13,625
Come on, sun!
Give it all you've got!

268
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:14,958
[sobs]

269
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,958
Hey, get over here
and do it with me!

270
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:19,375
[SAIKI] Wow, they aren't
even responding to Hairo.

271
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:21,208
They must really
be taking it hard.

272
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:22,458
[HAIRO] Where's your spirit?

273
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:23,916
[GIRL 7]
We're not in the mood.

274
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,333
[SAIKI]
Ouch.

275
00:09:25,416 --> 00:09:27,166
Even I can't bear
to watch this.

276
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:29,625
[wind rushes]

277
00:09:29,708 --> 00:09:31,208
Hey, the flight's
back on!

278
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:32,875
[BOY 6] The typhoon
just disappeared!

279
00:09:32,958 --> 00:09:35,375
[all cheer]
[BOY 7] Okinawa, here we come!

280
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:37,250
Oh, hey, Saiki,
where have you been?

281
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:38,875
Uh, you're
soaked...

282
00:09:38,958 --> 00:09:41,291
[SAIKI] Never mind that.
I just paid a little visit

283
00:09:41,375 --> 00:09:42,958
to a typhoon in Okinawa.

284
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:44,291
♪

285
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:46,250
Now, let
the school trip begin.

286
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:50,166
[man singing in Japanese]

287
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,375
♪

288
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:00,916
[HAIRO]
Liftoff!

289
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,291
[SAIKI]
It took some work,

290
00:10:02,375 --> 00:10:04,000
but the plane finally left
for Okinawa

291
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,375
with all the kids
on board.

292
00:10:05,458 --> 00:10:07,125
[STUDENT 2] I was worried
there for a sec.

293
00:10:07,208 --> 00:10:08,416
It'll make
a good story.

294
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,583
I'm glad the flight
wasn't canceled.

295
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:12,416
Yeah.
I almost started crying.

296
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:13,958
Hey, Teach!
Let's play <i>Uno!</i>

297
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,333
I'm pretty tough
to beat.

298
00:10:15,416 --> 00:10:16,875
Oh, yeah?
I bet I can beat you!

299
00:10:16,958 --> 00:10:18,291
Whoa, we're in
the sky!

300
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:20,000
Hey, how do I open
the window?

301
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:22,833
[SAIKI] I'm just glad everyone's
in good spirits again--

302
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:24,583
[groaning]

303
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:26,791
[SAIKI]
Well, almost everyone.

304
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:28,416
Kaidou,
are you all right?

305
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:30,291
[groans] Hold it together.
Yeah, I'm fine.

306
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:32,000
You need
motion sickness pills.

307
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,833
The flight attendant
gave me some earlier,

308
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,041
but they didn't help
at all.

309
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:36,333
I thought
I brought mine,

310
00:10:36,416 --> 00:10:37,708
but I left them
at my desk.

311
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,250
The flight's
two and a half hours.

312
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:40,500
I'll manage.

313
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:42,166
[KAIDOU] Just seeing
Teruhashi smile

314
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:43,250
made me feel better.

315
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,541
You okay, runt?

316
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:45,958
Why'd you start
puking

317
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:47,708
as soon as you
looked at my face?

318
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:49,333
[Saiki sighs]

319
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:51,666
[SAIKI] Just listening to that
makes me sick, too.

320
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:55,208
Good, I don't see
any here.

321
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:56,666
He's at that age,
so I feared

322
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,583
he might be
hiding dirty magazines,

323
00:10:58,666 --> 00:11:00,291
Looks like I was worried
for nothing.

324
00:11:00,375 --> 00:11:02,083
[SAIKI] Don't mind me.

325
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:06,083
Now what's this
about?

326
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:07,541
[KAIDOU]
I found 'em!

327
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:08,750
Didn't think they were in

328
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,083
the pocket
of my other clothes!

329
00:11:10,166 --> 00:11:11,250
I feel
much better now!

330
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:12,500
That's a relief!

331
00:11:12,583 --> 00:11:13,875
So you got a weak
stomach, runt?

332
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:15,333
[KAIDOU] Your face
makes me puke!

333
00:11:15,416 --> 00:11:17,166
[SAIKI] If you knew what
your mom just found

334
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:18,916
in your room,
you'd be sick again.

335
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,750
I'm exhausted.

336
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:22,416
Two round-trip
teleportations,

337
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:25,166
plus I wrestled a typhoon.
Time for a nap.

338
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:27,833
Oh, my!
Sir, are you all right?

339
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:29,458
[man groans]
What's with him?

340
00:11:29,541 --> 00:11:30,875
[SAIKI] Seriously.
What now?

341
00:11:30,958 --> 00:11:33,041
We've got a passenger
in distress here.

342
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:34,500
My stomach's
killing me!

343
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:35,750
You okay,
Takahashi?

344
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:37,208
[SAIKI] Oh, it's just
Takahashi.

345
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:38,708
Well, then,
goodnight.

346
00:11:38,791 --> 00:11:40,666
[ATTENDANT] Help! Is there
a doctor on board?

347
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:42,208
[STUDENT 3]
No! What'll we do?

348
00:11:42,291 --> 00:11:43,875
[ATTENDANT] We can land at
Fukuoka!

349
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:46,208
Like hell we will!
We've come too far.

350
00:11:46,291 --> 00:11:48,666
[SAIKI] One way or another,
we're making it to Okinawa.

351
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:50,666
I can't take it!
Get me off this plane!

352
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:52,166
[BOY 8] Just hold on!

353
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:53,583
[SAIKI]
Restore!

354
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:56,125
This pain!
It must be something serious--

355
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:57,708
Huh?
The pain is gone.

356
00:11:57,791 --> 00:11:58,916
[SAIKI] I didn't cure him.

357
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,416
I used my
restoration ability

358
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,208
to set his body
to yesterday's state.

359
00:12:02,291 --> 00:12:05,125
Which means he'll get the same
stomach pain again tomorrow.

360
00:12:05,208 --> 00:12:07,291
I'm gonna have
a great time in Okinawa now!

361
00:12:07,375 --> 00:12:08,875
[SAIKI]
Yeah, good luck with that.

362
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:11,541
[sighs] Had to use
my powers yet again.

363
00:12:11,625 --> 00:12:13,333
Now I really need
a nap.

364
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:14,875
[REPORTER]
Breaking news!

365
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:16,833
We have reports
of a terrible accident!

366
00:12:16,916 --> 00:12:18,875
A plane carrying students
on a school trip

367
00:12:18,958 --> 00:12:20,583
had to make an emergency
water landing.

368
00:12:20,666 --> 00:12:22,833
The downed aircraft
is Flight ASO-815.

369
00:12:22,916 --> 00:12:25,166
[SAIKI] They say that when
it rains, it pours,

370
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:27,291
but this is just
getting ridiculous.

371
00:12:27,375 --> 00:12:30,041
The plane is going to crash.

372
00:12:30,125 --> 00:12:31,458
That was a prophetic
dream.

373
00:12:31,541 --> 00:12:33,208
Should I try
my restoration power?

374
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:35,583
No, the plane may have had
the problem yesterday.

375
00:12:35,666 --> 00:12:37,750
I've gotta find out
what causes the crash first.

376
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:39,000
Gotta pee again?

377
00:12:39,083 --> 00:12:40,666
So we'll be landing soon?
Yeah.

378
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,625
Hm... Oh no,
that doesn't look good!

379
00:12:42,708 --> 00:12:45,041
The needle on that gauge
is spinning like crazy!

380
00:12:45,125 --> 00:12:46,916
[CAPTAIN] What? You mean
that gauge there?

381
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,375
What's happening?

382
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:50,541
Try pulling that lever
there or something?

383
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:52,000
[grunts]
It's not working!

384
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:53,625
It's not doing
anything!

385
00:12:53,708 --> 00:12:56,208
Try clicking those buttons
over there really fast!

386
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:58,250
Click, click, click!
We're losing altitude!

387
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:00,333
Oh, this is bad!
This is really bad!

388
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:02,083
If we don't do something quick,

389
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:04,166
the plane's gonna crash
in the water!

390
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:05,375
What's wrong?

391
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:07,166
That was a heck
of an earthquake.

392
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:09,208
Captain,
we're gaining altitude!

393
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:11,625
Really? Guess banging
stuff at random works!

394
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:14,208
Weird, the problem
isn't fixed, but...

395
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:15,916
[SAIKI] Oh, man.

396
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,833
This was easier than trying
to find the cause,

397
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:20,250
though it is kind of heavy.

398
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,875
Don't know how,
but we're flying.

399
00:13:21,958 --> 00:13:23,458
Let's land
while we can!

400
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:26,083
♪

401
00:13:26,166 --> 00:13:28,083
[NENDOU]
Woo-hoo! We're here!

402
00:13:28,166 --> 00:13:30,291
Hey, you don't
look so good, pal.

403
00:13:30,375 --> 00:13:32,000
Perk up bro.
[laughs]

404
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:34,333
So planes make you
motion sick, too?

405
00:13:34,416 --> 00:13:37,708
How many troubles do I have
to deal with on this trip?

406
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:40,000
♪

407
00:13:40,083 --> 00:13:41,333
[SAIKI]
Okinawa.

408
00:13:41,416 --> 00:13:44,041
The westernmost prefecture
in Japan.

409
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:46,333
It's one of the country's
top resorts,

410
00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:48,583
with beautiful views,
rich cultural heritage,

411
00:13:48,666 --> 00:13:50,208
and fantastic tourist spots.

412
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:52,041
And now our school trip--

413
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:54,166
[indistinct conversations]

414
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:56,958
[SAIKI] --can finally begin
for real.

415
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,791
♪

416
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:06,958
[SAIKI] I sure hope this
three-day trip goes smoothly.

417
00:14:07,041 --> 00:14:08,500
Whoa, cool!
Look, it's green!

418
00:14:08,583 --> 00:14:10,250
[SAIKI] So far I've seen
nothing but sea.

419
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:11,458
Somebody's
been dumping

420
00:14:11,541 --> 00:14:13,041
green paint
out there, right?

421
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:14,625
[SAIKI] Seriously?
Unfortunately,

422
00:14:14,708 --> 00:14:16,375
Nendou's not the only one
who's excited.

423
00:14:16,458 --> 00:14:17,916
Okinawa!
Crank up the heat!

424
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,958
[in unison] You're sweating
like crazy, Hairo!

425
00:14:20,041 --> 00:14:21,458
[SAIKI] Since we're on
vacation,

426
00:14:21,541 --> 00:14:23,083
everyone's
obnoxiously loud

427
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:24,375
[YUMEHARA] Tada!

428
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:26,041
Whoa, hey!
What're you doing?

429
00:14:26,125 --> 00:14:28,375
No worries. I'm wearing
a bathing suit underneath!

430
00:14:28,458 --> 00:14:29,583
Soki soba,
Aguu pork,

431
00:14:29,666 --> 00:14:31,333
goya champuru,
red bean soup.

432
00:14:31,416 --> 00:14:33,958
[SAIKI] At this point, Kaidou's
the only one keeping quiet.

433
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:35,541
Hey, runt,
you've had your nose

434
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:36,750
stuck in
that dang book

435
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:38,500
this whole time!
Try livin'.

436
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:40,041
You sure are
kashimashii today.

437
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:41,500
Wow, you weren't kidding!

438
00:14:41,583 --> 00:14:42,791
The sea is quite chura.

439
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:44,541
Chura?
[KAIDOU] Let's get some air.

440
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:46,916
Oh man, it's
ippee achisan outside!

441
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,291
Huh?
Ippei who?

442
00:14:48,375 --> 00:14:50,291
I know! You're using
Okinawan dialect.

443
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:51,666
Chimu dondon!

444
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,333
[YUMEHARA] I forgot
my shirt was open!

445
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:55,750
I'm speaking uchinaa guchi,
the Okinawan dialect.

446
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:57,416
Oh, that's right,
they use funny words

447
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:58,708
like "salsa"
and "menthol."

448
00:14:58,791 --> 00:15:00,375
[SAIKI] Pretty sure
you're wrong.

449
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:02,666
I think you meant "mensoore,"
which means "welcome."

450
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,000
"Kashimashii" means "noisy,"

451
00:15:04,083 --> 00:15:05,500
"chura" means "pretty,"

452
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:07,500
"ippee" means "very,"
"achisan" means "hot,"

453
00:15:07,583 --> 00:15:09,958
and "chimu dondon" means
"my heart goes pitter-patter."

454
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:12,166
You know a lot of words.
[KAIDOU] Wow! Teruhashi--

455
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:13,708
[TERUHASHI]
Will you teach me a few?

456
00:15:13,791 --> 00:15:14,791
Yeah, of course!

457
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:16,000
[SAIKI] Great, now Kaidou's

458
00:15:16,083 --> 00:15:17,375
the most excited kid of all.

459
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,833
[TOUR GUIDE]
Everybody, time for lunch.

460
00:15:19,916 --> 00:15:22,291
[NENDOU]
Uh, so this is Okinawan soba?

461
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:23,375
It don't look
like soba.

462
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:24,625
They call it "soba,"

463
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:26,208
but they don't use
buckwheat flour.

464
00:15:26,291 --> 00:15:27,875
Whatever it is,
looks good! Let's eat!

465
00:15:27,958 --> 00:15:29,333
Kuwacchii sabira.

466
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:30,583
[groans]

467
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:32,500
Oh, wow! This is maasan!

468
00:15:32,583 --> 00:15:33,958
This soba is ippee maasan!

469
00:15:34,041 --> 00:15:35,416
[SAIKI]
Teruhashi complimented

470
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,250
his language skills earlier,

471
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:38,791
so now he's going overboard.

472
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:40,416
[KAIDOU]
Eat up, guys! It's maasan!

473
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,666
[BOTH]
That's getting really annoying.

474
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:44,583
[KAIDOU] Whoa, Mera,
you're a gachimayaa!

475
00:15:44,666 --> 00:15:46,083
Hm? Hm!

476
00:15:46,166 --> 00:15:48,250
This soba's so darn maasan
that nada sousou.

477
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,041
For those who don't know,

478
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:52,708
"maasan" means "delicious,"
"gachimayaa" means "glutton,"

479
00:15:52,791 --> 00:15:54,708
and "nada sousou" means
"tears trickle down."

480
00:15:54,791 --> 00:15:56,375
[SAIKI] The kid's trying
way too hard.

481
00:15:56,458 --> 00:15:58,291
Uh, wow, that's
impressive, Kaidou.

482
00:15:58,375 --> 00:16:00,166
I can't even keep track
of them all.

483
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,125
No need to worry.
Even if you don't get

484
00:16:02,208 --> 00:16:04,291
uchinaa guchi,
nankuru naisa!

485
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:06,375
[SAIKI] "Nankuru naisa" means
"it'll work out."

486
00:16:06,458 --> 00:16:07,916
He's been dying
to use that.

487
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,500
[NENDOU] I ate a lot!
That was good!

488
00:16:09,583 --> 00:16:10,833
Kuwacchii sabitan.

489
00:16:10,916 --> 00:16:12,541
[YUMEHARA] Hey, we have
some time left.

490
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:14,166
Wanna check out
some souvenir shops?

491
00:16:14,250 --> 00:16:15,375
Yeah, let's go!
[gasps]

492
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:18,541
