gaze upon

499
00:16:28,708 --> 00:16:30,250
the fiercest creatures
in Yanbaru?

500
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:32,083
[SAIKI]
This mode's annoying, too.

501
00:16:32,166 --> 00:16:33,500
Whoa!
What's this place?

502
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,083
It looks pretty sweet!
Hah, hah!

503
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,916
[SAIKI] Not interested.
Maybe I'll join up

504
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,750
with the girls.
[Yumehara screams]

505
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,791
Chisato, you're not
supposed to eat

506
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:42,291
that many
of the free samples!

507
00:16:42,375 --> 00:16:43,708
But this pineapple
is so juicy!

508
00:16:43,791 --> 00:16:44,833
Gachimayaa!

509
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:46,291
People started
gathering around

510
00:16:46,375 --> 00:16:47,291
for some reason.

511
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:48,291
[MAN 1] Chura Kaaghii!

512
00:16:48,375 --> 00:16:49,375
[MAN 2] Chee-moo dondon!

513
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:50,833
[SAIKI]
The ultimate death match

514
00:16:50,916 --> 00:16:52,625
in Yanbaru
sounds pretty good.

515
00:16:52,708 --> 00:16:55,666
[OWNER] Howdy, and welcome to
the Habu vs. Mongoose show!

516
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,125
[NENDOU] Snake!
Oh, don't worry.

517
00:16:57,208 --> 00:17:00,083
This snake is my friend.
He would never bite you.

518
00:17:00,166 --> 00:17:02,541
Ah! Snake!
Get it off me!

519
00:17:02,625 --> 00:17:05,750
It'll bite!
[SAIKI] Nankuru naisa.

520
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,458
[OWNER] If you encounter a habu,
you'll wanna run away fast.

521
00:17:08,541 --> 00:17:10,208
Can you guess
where they'd bite ya first?

522
00:17:10,291 --> 00:17:12,000
The legs?
That's right!

523
00:17:12,083 --> 00:17:13,916
They want their fangs
in your shanks.

524
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,708
Just a little rhyme
I made up.

525
00:17:15,791 --> 00:17:18,166
If you run into a habu snake,
ask if it has poison.

526
00:17:18,250 --> 00:17:20,041
It'll tell ya,
"yes, I snake it in."

527
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:21,541
[OWNER] Just kidding.
[all groan]

528
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:22,791
How about this one?

529
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,583
What makes a habu
so charming--

530
00:17:24,666 --> 00:17:26,166
[SAIKI]
He doesn't know when to quit.

531
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:27,708
Its poise!
Poisonous? You get it?

532
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,416
♪

533
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,375
Well, here's the Habu
Versus Mongoose match.

534
00:17:31,458 --> 00:17:33,333
What?
You mean they're not here?

535
00:17:33,416 --> 00:17:34,875
[OWNER]
Ain't like the old days.

536
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:36,500
Got animal protection
laws now.

537
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:38,416
So the outcome's
already decided?

538
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,833
[SAIKI] It was a 3-minute
video.

539
00:17:39,916 --> 00:17:41,916
And as expected,
the mongoose won.

540
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,291
I wanna go.
Me too.

541
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:44,625
[OWNER] Wait,
not so fast.

542
00:17:44,708 --> 00:17:46,791
Ippee maasan
makes a great souvenir.

543
00:17:46,875 --> 00:17:48,375
[SAIKI]
Should've seen that coming.

544
00:17:48,458 --> 00:17:49,833
I don't wanna
carry it around.

545
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:52,875
Nankuru naisa. How 'bout
habu powder and oil?

546
00:17:52,958 --> 00:17:55,000
[SAIKI]
The guy continued his pitch

547
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:56,625
for 20 minutes.
By the end--

548
00:17:56,708 --> 00:17:59,083
[KAIDOU]
Nada sousou.

549
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:02,000
[SAIKI] --Kaidou walked away
with all of it.

550
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:03,041
♪ Come on! ♪

551
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:04,791
[man singing in Japanese]

552
00:18:07,583 --> 00:18:09,833
♪

553
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:13,500
[HAIRO]
Dinner's at 18:00

554
00:18:13,583 --> 00:18:15,166
in the first floor
dining hall!

555
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:17,333
Each class has 20 minutes
to take a bath.

556
00:18:17,416 --> 00:18:19,750
After, we'll have free time,
but don't leave the hotel.

557
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,375
[STUDENT 4] This is a swanky
hotel.

558
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:23,958
[SAIKI] Thank goodness
the first day's almost over.

559
00:18:24,041 --> 00:18:25,375
Wish I could relax,

560
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:28,041
but the real hell's
about to start.

561
00:18:28,125 --> 00:18:30,500
[NENDOU]
We can see the sea from here!

562
00:18:30,583 --> 00:18:32,166
Huh. Wow, this room
isn't so bad.

563
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:33,500
[SAIKI] Least I don't
see bugs.

564
00:18:33,583 --> 00:18:35,333
Don't block
the entrance way.

565
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,500
First, Teruhashi
ditches our group,

566
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:40,708
then we get stuck in a room with
you losers. Sucks to be us!

567
00:18:40,791 --> 00:18:42,125
We're putting
our stuff here.

568
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:43,583
[SAIKI]
Old guy got to you, too?

569
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:45,333
Don't get down,
Takahashi.

570
00:18:45,416 --> 00:18:47,333
We can still
have fun here.

571
00:18:47,416 --> 00:18:49,333
Oh, yeah, I forgot
about the great views.

572
00:18:49,416 --> 00:18:51,875
What's with them?
Are they up to something?

573
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:53,375
[SAIKI] Yeah, something
stupid.

574
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:54,625
Mm-mm!

575
00:18:54,708 --> 00:18:56,291
[KAIDOU]
You sure like to eat, Mera.

576
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:58,416
She ate
all my snacks, too.

577
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,708
More rice,
please!

578
00:18:59,791 --> 00:19:01,458
So where are we
going tomorrow?

579
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,375
Let's see, first up
is the pineapple garden.

580
00:19:03,458 --> 00:19:04,833
[MERA] Drool.
Pineapple garden?

581
00:19:04,916 --> 00:19:06,250
How are you hungry
while eating?

582
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,083
Then after,
the famous aquarium!

583
00:19:08,166 --> 00:19:09,375
[MERA] Fish? Drool.

584
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:11,041
[SAIKI]
Those fish aren't for eating.

585
00:19:11,125 --> 00:19:12,875
[TERUHASHI]
The first day's almost done.

586
00:19:12,958 --> 00:19:14,791
Feels like the trip
will be over in no time.

587
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:16,500
[YUMEHARA]
What are you talking about?

588
00:19:16,583 --> 00:19:17,750
It's barely even begun!

589
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:19,083
Yeah, you're right.

590
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:20,250
Shall we go
take a bath now?

591
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:21,708
[giggles]
Sounds good.

592
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:23,625
They're acting weird.
What are they up to?

593
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:24,916
[SAIKI] Something stupid.

594
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,250
[TAKAHASHI]
Hah, hah! Now this

595
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:27,708
is what a school trip's
all about!

596
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,833
[ALL]
Looking at girls!

597
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:31,083
What's the plan?

598
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:32,708
I scoped the place
out last week.

599
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:34,000
You flew
all the way here?

600
00:19:34,083 --> 00:19:35,458
They swap
men's and women's baths

601
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:37,083
every other day.
I have a good grasp

602
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:38,166
of the other side.

603
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:39,708
That's dedication!

604
00:19:39,791 --> 00:19:41,416
Yeah,
I don't know what to say.

605
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:43,083
It'll all be worth it soon

606
00:19:43,166 --> 00:19:45,875
as we catch a glimpse of her!

607
00:19:45,958 --> 00:19:47,750
Best place
to sneak a peek is there.

608
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:49,375
We can sit on each other's
shoulders!

609
00:19:49,458 --> 00:19:51,958
[TAKAHASHI] I don't want you
on my shoulders naked!

610
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:53,958
I brought three.
[BOTH] Whoa!

611
00:19:54,041 --> 00:19:55,666
[TAKAHASHI] All right!
Let's do this!

612
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:57,333
Steamy Reality
Scope!

613
00:19:58,583 --> 00:19:59,791
[all scream]

614
00:19:59,875 --> 00:20:01,750
Why are you showing up
in our view?

615
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:03,250
Let's try again!

616
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:04,750
What are those?

617
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:06,375
[TAKAHASHI]
What the hell is wrong

618
00:20:06,458 --> 00:20:08,083
with these stupid
periscopes?

619
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:09,333
[SAIKI] That's what you get

620
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:10,708
for trying to peep on girls.

621
00:20:10,791 --> 00:20:12,250
Not taking
your glasses off?

622
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:14,125
What's so great
about seeing naked bodies?

623
00:20:14,208 --> 00:20:15,916
[KAIDOU] They're foggy.
[SAIKI] I see 'em

624
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,166
all the time, and they
don't seem that special.

625
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:19,916
[NENDOU]
This thing is amazing!

626
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,166
[TAKAHASHI] Shut up, Nendou!

627
00:20:21,250 --> 00:20:23,166
And get your grubby--
[all gasp]

628
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:24,583
[TAKAHASHI]
It's not possible.

629
00:20:24,666 --> 00:20:25,833
[YOKOTA] I'm never gonna make

630
00:20:25,916 --> 00:20:27,083
fun of Nendou again.

631
00:20:27,166 --> 00:20:28,750
They ain't looked at me
since the bath.

632
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:30,541
[SAIKI]
They're idiots. Just ignore 'em.

633
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:32,083
[YUMEHARA]
One, two. Good evening!

634
00:20:32,166 --> 00:20:34,125
Let's play <i>Uno!</i>

635
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:36,375
A bunch of guys showed up
at our room for some reason,

636
00:20:36,458 --> 00:20:38,000
so is it cool
if we hang out in yours?

637
00:20:38,083 --> 00:20:39,625
[YUMEHARA]
That was perfect!

638
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:41,375
[TERUHASHI]
Yeah, we nailed the timing!

639
00:20:41,458 --> 00:20:43,625
[YUMEHARA] That's enough
practice, let's go for it!

640
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:46,750
[SAIKI] Sorry, girls,
but I'm not really into <i>Uno.</i>

641
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:48,333
[sighs]

642
00:20:48,416 --> 00:20:50,333
I should be safe here.

643
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:51,833
Man, I'm beat.

644
00:20:51,916 --> 00:20:53,583
When I made
that typhoon disappear

645
00:20:53,666 --> 00:20:54,958
and when I carried
the plane,

646
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:57,166
I removed my
control device both times,

647
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,250
so it's gonna be
a long trip.

648
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:00,833
[TERUHASHI]
Seriously, where could

649
00:21:00,916 --> 00:21:02,291
Saiki have gone?
And why am I,

650
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:04,541
the most perfect girl,
wandering around sear--

651
00:21:04,625 --> 00:21:06,791
Oh! Saiki!
Is he asleep?

652
00:21:06,875 --> 00:21:08,583
Yes!
This is my chance!

653
00:21:08,666 --> 00:21:10,625
Before he wakes up.

654
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:12,208
Wait, what was I just
about to do?

655
00:21:12,291 --> 00:21:14,500
How could I, the world's
most perfect pretty girl,

656
00:21:14,583 --> 00:21:16,666
do the kind of thing
a creepy, gross, unpopular guy

657
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:18,166
would do to a girl
like me?

658
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:20,041
[KURUMI]
Wonder if Kuu's doing okay.

659
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:21,041
Why is that?

660
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:22,458
He might have an accident.

661
00:21:22,541 --> 00:21:24,166
He hasn't done that
since fourth grade.

662
00:21:24,250 --> 00:21:25,625
[KURUMI] Was it
the fifth grade?

663
00:21:25,708 --> 00:21:27,166
Around the time
he started wearing

664
00:21:27,250 --> 00:21:29,250
that thing on his head.
[KUNIHARU] You're right.

665
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:31,708
If that's what's preventing him
from having an accident,

666
00:21:31,791 --> 00:21:33,208
what'll happen
if it comes off?

667
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:34,791
Heh, heh! You worry
too much, honey.

668
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:36,083
Guess you're right.

669
00:21:36,166 --> 00:21:38,041
[TERUHASHI] Here we go.
Hope it's okay

670
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:39,666
I took it off
without asking.

671
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:41,333
But if he fell on it,
this hairpin

672
00:21:41,416 --> 00:21:44,333
could really
hurt him, so-- Huh?

673
00:21:44,416 --> 00:21:46,375
Saiki, wake up!
We got a big problem!

674
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:48,166
[SAIKI] What?
I must've fallen asleep.

675
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:50,375
This is no time
to be taking a nap!

676
00:21:50,458 --> 00:21:52,375
[SAIKI] Stop yelling in my ear.
What time is it?

677
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:53,666
We have to return
to the hotel.

678
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:55,458
You mean
return the hotel!

679
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:57,416
[SAIKI] What? No, I meant
return to the hotel.

680
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,083
Now calm down.
[TORITSUKA] Calm down?

681
00:21:59,166 --> 00:22:00,500
Are you out of
your mind?

682
00:22:00,583 --> 00:22:02,208
The hotel we were
staying in is gone!

683
00:22:02,291 --> 00:22:03,791
And I've got
a pretty good feeling

684
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:05,500
that you're
behind this somehow!

685
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:11,625
[SAIKI] Oops,
I had an accident.

686
00:22:13,541 --> 00:22:15,333
♪

687
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:23,541
[woman singing in Japanese]

688
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,583
[SAIKI]
Our school trip has been

689
00:23:43,666 --> 00:23:45,083
one disaster after another.

690
00:23:45,166 --> 00:23:46,833
Then I had to go
and have an accident,

691
00:23:46,916 --> 00:23:48,500
making it even worse.

692
00:23:48,583 --> 00:23:51,333
Next time on <i>The Disastrous</i>
<i>Life of Saiki K.:</i>

693
00:23:51,416 --> 00:23:52,958
Our Okinawa adventure
continues.

694
00:23:53,041 --> 00:23:54,916
Unfortunately for me.

